VUMA FM presenter Jacinta Ngobese is set to represent South Africa in Washington DC, USA. On Facebook, the Wear Your Crown movement ambassador announced she was chosen as one of the most influential people in the world. “I’m truly humbled to be invited to Washington DC to represent SA as an ambassador for the #wearyourcrown movement. Thanks to Jayshree Mallaya for choosing me as one of the most influential people in the world. This beautiful piece of art was painted by international award-winning painter Ramona Pintea, and will be displayed as part of this project at Hotel Zena.” The milestone was celebrated by her friends and colleagues. ALSO READ : TRIBUTES POUR IN FOR KULI ROBERTS! Sihle Mvundla wrote: “A vision pursued is indeed a vision achieved. A lot is coming your way and it’s going to be fantastic. You might not notice it but the world sees it.” Stakeholder Jayshree posted: “So excited to have beautiful and talented Jacinta represent our non-profit organisation @overthewallstogether in the #wearyourcrown in Washington DC. Taking South Africa to the world.” Mbusoh Ngobese commented: “Congratulations, Jacinta. I am happy for you indeed. You are influential to the people of the world, halala!” 